From 14cf7952f1a4d77b82d45b19bf36516515695501 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thirusenthil Kumaran J <thirusen@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 14 Jul 2025 12:43:44 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: PROTOCOL: cfg80211: mac80211: Store 6 GHz power
 mode per link.

Currently, the 6 GHz power mode is stored at an interface level within
the wdev structure. This does not work for multi-link devices where each
6 GHz link can have a different power mode.

To fix this, store the 6 GHz power mode in the link structure.
Add code changes across mac80211 and cfg80211 to support this.
  (1) Add a new field he_6ghz_power_type in the ap settings for parsing
      and storing the 6 GHz power mode send by the user space.
  (2) Copy the power mode configured in the settings to the
      corresponding link's ieee80211_bss_conf structure.
  (3) Modify the API 'ieee80211_get_ap_6ghz_pwr_mode' to return the
      6 GHz power mode for the specific link.
  (4) Update mac80211 APIs to take link id as an additional argument
      to look up the 6 GHz power mode for the specific link.

Fixes: None
Patch-work: None
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY
Feature: AFC
Patch-dependency:
subsys/0048-cfg80211-mac80211-regulatory-awgn-and-6g-channel-cha.patch

Signed-off-by: Thirusenthil Kumaran J <thirusen@qti.qualcomm.com>
